        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:02PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 302 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Alice Acres, or near Alice, moving southeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kingsville, Alice, Robstown, San Diego, Driscoll, Bishop, Orange
Grove, San Patricio, Midway, Alfred-South La Paloma, Bluntzer,
Banquete, Westdale, Ben Bolt, Sandia, Tecalote, Alice Acres, Alfred,
Agua Dulce, and North San Pedro.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 281 between mile markers 656 and 682.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 674 and 684, and between mile
markers 688 and 696.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
